Name: Alex
Video_Title: The Truth About Electronic Cigarettes (a.k.a. Vape Products)
Description:
this 2019 michigan department of health and human services webinar presents information about electronic cigarettes, also called e-cigarettes or vape products.  

elaine lyon and carolyn chaudhary, both public health consultants in the mdhhs tobacco section, explain the basics of e-cigarettes, including how they work, what they look like, and how you can recognize them. they also talk about the types of public health consequences and the safety and health concerns posed by e-cigarettes.  the presenters also discuss what makes e-cigarettes especially attractive to youth in our state.  resources are also provided for those who want to learn more about this important health topic.

for more information about e-cigarettes, visit https://www.michigan.gov/e-cigarettes.

preheating (warms oil at 1.1-1.8 volts prepping it for a better vape)

5 clicks to turn on/off

red light = 3.8volts
blue light = 4.0volts

universal 510 tread compatible with liquid gold c02 oil cartridges
